<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900726-0070</DOCNO><DOCID>900726-0070.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Rohr Industries Inc.:   Pact With Airbus Industrie   For Housings Is Expanded</HL><DATE>07/26/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   U.BA F.ASP F.ABI RHR</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><LP>   Rohr Industries Inc. said it reached a follow-on agreementwith European manufacturer Airbus Industrie to supply enginehousing systems for 800 airliners.   The agreement is valued at more than $1 billion.</LP><TEXT>   It calls for Rohr to furnish engine housing, or nacelle,systems for engines on two models of Airbus airliners, theA-320 and the A-321, initially in early 1992.   The A-321 is a stretched derivative of the currentA-320-200 aircraft. Currently, Rohr is supplying nacellesystems for 200 Airbus A-320 airliners under a 1984 contract.The follow-on agreement expands the program to cover 1,000airliners.   Airbus Industrie is an aircraft manufacturing consortiumowned by Aerospatiale of France, Deutsche Airbus of WestGermany, British Aerospace PLC of Britain and ConstruccionesAeronauticas S.A. of Spain.   Chula Vista, Calif.-based Rohr designs, manufactures andsupports aircraft engine nacelle systems and parts forcommercial, military and business aircraft.</TEXT></DOC>